    thinking: "**Designing the App Interface**\n\nI\'m now diving into the application\'s design. The immediate goal is an Android Jetpack Compose liquor tasting journal app. My focus is an elegant, interactive React interface that includes an interactive Android Phone Simulator.\n\n\n**Simulating the App**\n\nI\'ve been working on a highly-styled smartphone frame to simulate the app\'s use. It\'s a key interactive React element, which will be the app\'s visual centerpiece. The simulator will run a realistic Android app simulation, focusing on the core experience. I\'m prioritizing the main screens: a home screen with a tasting list, complete with quick filter tabs and a FAB for adding tastings, and the add/edit screen with form fields and flavor profile sliders.\n\n\n**Developing the UI Elements**\n\nNow, I\'m concentrating on the detail screen\'s design. I\'m aiming for a visually appealing liquor review, complete with a flavor chart \342\200\223 perhaps a radar or animated progress bars. There will be a quick summary of essential data like rating, ABV, and notes. Navigation will be simple with a back button and a delete option. Then, the Jetpack Compose Code Exporter Panel will allow for a user to see the production-ready code with an interactive file viewer.\n\n\n**Organizing the Code Components**\n\nI\'m now determining the directory structure and the components. I will create a phone simulator and code viewer, and I will implement a template storage to organize and maintain well-crafted Kotlin templates to facilitate ease of use. I\'m focusing on features such as code copying, file downloads, syntax highlighting, and interactive syncing between the simulator and the code viewer.\n\n\n**Defining the Data Structures**\n\nI\'m now establishing core data structures. Specifically, I am crafting high-quality Compose code templates that compile flawlessly in Android Studio. These templates will use Jetpack Compose, Material 3, and standard Jetpack Navigation. I\'m focusing on key files, including `MainActivity.kt`, `TastingModels.kt`, `TastingListScreen.kt`, `TastingDetailScreen.kt`, and `TastingFormScreen.kt`. The goal is to provide a solid foundation for the app\'s structure. I\'m prioritizing data models like `TastingEntry`, the enum `LiquorCategory`, and dummy data for easy setup, along with navigation via `NavHost`.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 43979883
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
