    thinking: "**Detailing UI Components**\n\nI\'m now detailing the user interface components. I am planning `src/components/PhoneSimulator.tsx` to handle the phone mockup, and interactivity with the listings. This includes adding and viewing notes, among other features. The plan is becoming clearer, and the direction for development is defined.\n\n\n**Defining Simulator Features**\n\nI\'m solidifying the simulator\'s feature set. It will present a premium Android device mockup, allowing users to view, search, and filter tasting entries with beautiful icons. The detail view will display smooth animated progress bars. It will also have delete functionality, a floating action button to add entries, and interactive input forms for new entries, with sliders. Added entries will persist in `localStorage`.\n\n\n**Implementing Screen Transitions**\n\nI\'ve got an *excellent* idea: When the user switches screens, an `onScreenChange(screenName)` event will fire, and the main app can switch to the correct file in the code editor! It\'s an *amazing* DX feature that will make this simulator incredibly engaging. Let\'s make sure `/src/components/PhoneSimulator.tsx` is *gorgeous* with smooth `motion` animations! Let\'s import all the `lucide-react` icons we\'ll need, and start building!\n\n\n"
