    thinking: "**Developing CodeViewer Component**\n\nI\'m now focused on the `CodeViewer.tsx` component and the architecture of displaying Jetpack Compose files. I envision an IDE-like interface with tabs for each file, specifically `TastingModels.kt`, `MainActivity.kt`, and `TastingNotes.kt`, to start. The structure needs to be intuitive.\n\n\n**Expanding CodeViewer Features**\n\nI\'m now integrating new features for the `CodeViewer` component, expanding its functionality. I\'m focusing on adding tabs for `TastingListScreen.kt`, `TastingFormScreen.kt`, `TastingDetailScreen.kt`, and `Theme.kt`. I\'m also implementing stylized line numbers and syntax highlighting for Kotlin, mirroring an Android Studio environment, to enhance the visual appeal. Additionally, I\'m working on \"Copy\" and \"Download All Files\" buttons for convenience and exploring the potential for seamless synchronization with a simulator screen.\n\n\n"
